<subsection xml:id="subsec-rates" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Rates</title>

   <introduction>
        <p>
            A rate is a ratio that compares two quantities measured in different units. 
            For example, if a car travels 100 miles in 2 hours, 
            the rate is <m>\frac{100 \, \text{miles}}{2 \, \text{hours}}</m> <m>= 50</m> miles per hour.
        </p>
   </introduction>
    

